    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "but that's just circular reasoning. saying i have value because i exist is just a feeling, not a fact. if we look at the actual outcome, there's no net gain in the universe. if the sum of all experiences ends in entropy anyway, then the equation of life vs death is basically zero. why should i fight for a positive value that doesn't even exist?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
