      "content": "exactly. so if the net value is zero, then choosing to end it isn't even a \"bad\" choice or a tragedy. it's just a neutral move to reach that zero state faster. if the math holds up, isn't it just more efficient to accept the nothingness now rather than dragging out the entropy?",
